01:52.863 --> 01:54.897
♪ Da, da, da, da, da ♪

01:54.898 --> 01:56.933
♪ da, da, da, da, da ♪

01:56.934 --> 02:00.803
♪ da-da, da-da, da-da ♪

02:02.973 --> 02:05.841
Hey, Cassie.
I left you a message.

02:05.842 --> 02:08.009
Uh, yeah, sorry.
I've been busy.

02:08.011 --> 02:09.578
Is everything all right?

02:09.579 --> 02:11.914
I was thinking we could
hang out tonight.

02:11.915 --> 02:13.616
Maybe we could talk
about what's been going on.

02:13.617 --> 02:16.151
Thanks, but I can't.

02:16.152 --> 02:18.921
What's wrong, Cassie?
Did I do something?

02:20.790 --> 02:23.792
I did your binding ritual
to get our powers under control

02:23.793 --> 02:25.160
so no one else
would get hurt.

02:25.161 --> 02:28.130
That doesn't mean we all need
to be friends.

02:28.131 --> 02:30.165
I know. But we can be.

02:30.166 --> 02:31.300
Or at least
you and I can.

02:31.301 --> 02:32.601
I don't like the secrets.

02:32.602 --> 02:34.203
And I don't like
lying to Sally

02:34.204 --> 02:35.571
about what really happened.

02:35.572 --> 02:37.589
This whole thing--
it's--it's too weird!

02:37.590 --> 02:40.392
I know. Which why I think
we should stick together.

02:40.393 --> 02:41.493
I'm sorry, Diana.

02:41.494 --> 02:44.529
It's the way it has to be.

02:52.738 --> 02:56.441
I like this...
Skipping school.

02:56.442 --> 02:58.843
Me, too.

02:58.844 --> 03:02.580
Hey, um...
I have this idea.

03:02.581 --> 03:04.616
It's gonna sound
kind of crazy.

03:04.617 --> 03:09.220
But there's this stupid
dance tomorrow.

03:09.221 --> 03:11.523
And I was thinking
we should go.

03:11.524 --> 03:14.058
You and me.

03:15.594 --> 03:18.696
You wanna shower first?
Or do you want me to go?

03:18.697 --> 03:20.698
That's all you
got to say?

03:20.699 --> 03:21.666
I just asked you out.

03:21.667 --> 03:24.636
You said we were just sex,
Melissa.

03:24.637 --> 03:26.971
You didn't want
anyone to know about us.

03:26.972 --> 03:28.606
I didn't want people
to think I was slutty.

03:28.607 --> 03:30.642
Then why do you want to go
to the dance together?

03:30.643 --> 03:32.444
Because I'm feeling
kind of slutty.

03:32.445 --> 03:34.712
What if Faye finds out?

03:34.713 --> 03:36.648
Maybe I'm ok
with it now.

03:36.649 --> 03:38.550
It's just
a school dance.

03:38.551 --> 03:40.618
I don't do dances.

03:40.619 --> 03:42.187
I just thought it would
be nice to do something

03:42.188 --> 03:43.755
that doesn't
involve sex.

03:43.756 --> 03:45.223
We're not dating, Melissa.

03:45.224 --> 03:48.560
If that's where
this is going, we're done.

03:48.561 --> 03:50.395
You're dick!

03:53.299 --> 03:55.900
I know your secret.

03:55.901 --> 03:57.602
What?

03:57.603 --> 04:01.473
You haven't signed up for any
extracurriculars.

04:01.474 --> 04:04.309
Oh. Right. I forgot.

04:04.310 --> 04:07.579
So I was hoping you could
help me with the dance.

04:07.580 --> 04:10.148
My streamer hanging arm
has seen better days.

04:10.149 --> 04:11.483
Yes, sure.
Whatever I can do.

04:11.484 --> 04:13.785
I'm just--
I'm glad you're ok.

04:15.287 --> 04:17.988
Last night was crazy, huh?

04:17.990 --> 04:20.492
The doctor said
I was really lucky.

04:20.493 --> 04:23.528
I never actually
saw what happened.

04:23.529 --> 04:27.031
Me neither.
It was all a blur.

04:27.032 --> 04:32.470
But I keep getting
these flashes of Faye.

04:32.471 --> 04:34.539
Like she did it.

04:34.540 --> 04:38.243
Faye?! How?
That's impossible.

04:38.244 --> 04:39.844
I know it sounds crazy.

04:39.845 --> 04:45.483
But I have this distinct memory
of her giving me her bitch stare

04:45.484 --> 04:47.385
and then me waking up
on the rocks.

04:47.386 --> 04:49.621
Wow. She gives me
that stare every day.

04:49.622 --> 04:52.156
Maybe I should start wearing
a helmet to school.

04:52.157 --> 04:54.893
I know.
It's ridiculous, right?

04:54.894 --> 04:57.762
I refuse to let that
girl get inside my head.

04:57.763 --> 04:59.564
Forget I said anything.

05:03.402 --> 05:04.969
Hey, Adam.

05:04.970 --> 05:06.204
Hey.

05:06.205 --> 05:08.706
So tell me about
this new Cassie girl.

05:08.707 --> 05:09.941
What about her?

05:09.942 --> 05:10.909
I've seen you talking
to her.

05:10.910 --> 05:11.843
Is she friends
with Diana?

05:11.844 --> 05:13.311
What do you want, Luke?

05:13.312 --> 05:14.846
An introduction.

05:14.847 --> 05:16.414
No, I don't think so.

05:16.415 --> 05:17.649
She's going through a hard time
right now, all right?

05:17.650 --> 05:18.950
Yeah, I know the story.

05:18.951 --> 05:20.885
Her mom's died.
Lives with her grandmother.

05:20.886 --> 05:24.789
She's bummin'. Maybe she
could use someone to talk to.

05:24.790 --> 05:25.990
Have a good time.

05:25.991 --> 05:29.794
Sure. Yeah, I guess.

05:29.795 --> 05:31.362
Yes!

05:34.633 --> 05:37.068
Things go smoothly?

05:38.871 --> 05:42.040
Henry's body is
at the lake house.

05:42.041 --> 05:44.776
It won't be found
until it needs to be.

05:46.979 --> 05:48.680
Thank you, Charles.

05:48.681 --> 05:51.416
Henry brought this
on himself, Dawn.

05:51.417 --> 05:53.985
You had no choice.

05:53.986 --> 05:57.522
Doesn't make it
any easier.

05:57.523 --> 06:00.391
He was Faye's
grandfather.

06:01.527 --> 06:03.261
Well, I searched Henry's house.

06:03.262 --> 06:05.229
There was no sign
of a crystal.

06:09.368 --> 06:11.669
I watched the whole thing.

06:11.670 --> 06:13.605
The circle is bound.

06:13.606 --> 06:15.239
We have to move fast,
Charles.

06:15.240 --> 06:19.477
Before someone
else catches on to us.

06:19.478 --> 06:22.113
There are still people in this
town who remember...

06:28.654 --> 06:30.955
Hey, honey.

06:30.956 --> 06:33.691
What are you doing here,
Dad?

06:33.692 --> 06:35.423
Some budget wrangling.

06:35.448 --> 06:36.648
You know I handle all
the school's legal work.

06:36.729 --> 06:37.829
Do you need a ride home?

06:37.830 --> 06:38.963
No, I'm good.

06:38.964 --> 06:41.265
Ok. I'll see you
at home.

06:46.805 --> 06:48.640
He's so cute.

06:48.641 --> 06:49.641
But taken.

06:49.642 --> 06:52.543
No, the other cute one.
I know Adam's taken.

06:53.812 --> 06:55.313
- Hey.
- Hey.

06:55.314 --> 06:56.414
Glad to see you're
up and around.

06:56.415 --> 06:57.882
Thanks Adam.

06:57.883 --> 07:00.462
Uh, Cassie, I want you
to meet a friend of mine.

07:00.463 --> 07:01.160
This is Luke.

07:01.161 --> 07:03.421
Hi, Cassie.
Nice to meet you.

07:03.491 --> 07:04.758
Yeah, you too.

07:04.793 --> 07:06.700
If you ever need someone
to show you around

07:06.701 --> 07:08.535
or you just wanna hang out,

07:08.761 --> 07:10.662
I'm available.

07:12.031 --> 07:14.666
I'll see you guys,
later.

07:14.667 --> 07:15.800
Heh.

07:19.204 --> 07:21.806
Yeah, me too.
I'll see you later.

07:26.378 --> 07:28.680
You know, there's
a dance tomorrow night?

07:28.681 --> 07:30.748
Yeah, I'm helping
Sally with it.

07:30.749 --> 07:31.916
Decorating committee.

07:31.917 --> 07:34.152
So, you're going.
With anyone?

07:34.153 --> 07:35.520
Sally.

07:35.521 --> 07:37.155
Right. Obviously.

07:37.156 --> 07:39.390
But, you know,
with her sling,

07:39.391 --> 07:41.893
it's probably gonna be
hard for her to dance.

07:41.894 --> 07:45.530
So I could fill in
for her.

07:45.531 --> 07:47.598
If you want.

07:47.599 --> 07:52.737
Uh, that's my awkward
way of asking you to the dance.

07:52.738 --> 07:55.206
Well, I appreciate you asking.

07:55.207 --> 07:56.641
Mm-hmm.

07:56.642 --> 07:58.976
But I have never decorated
a school dance before,

07:58.977 --> 08:01.546
much less attended.

08:01.547 --> 08:03.681
Rain check?

08:03.682 --> 08:06.718
Yeah, sure.

08:10.756 --> 08:14.759
There you go.

08:20.833 --> 08:23.201
The projector is being
set up in the afternoon.

08:23.202 --> 08:24.936
And most of the lights
are already up.

08:24.937 --> 08:27.638
We have to go over music
with the DJ.

08:28.941 --> 08:32.477
We also need 4 circular tables
from the cafeteria

08:32.477 --> 08:35.246
and then all the stackable chairs
we can get.

08:35.246 --> 08:37.749
So Luke asked you
to the dance.

08:37.750 --> 08:40.985
Sort of. I guess.

08:40.986 --> 08:42.820
But you turned him down.

08:42.821 --> 08:44.255
Kind of.

08:44.256 --> 08:46.724
Because you can't stop
staring at Adam?

08:46.725 --> 08:50.094
What? No. Not at all.

08:50.095 --> 08:53.798
Adam is dating...Diana.

08:53.799 --> 08:59.270
And yet for some reason he can't
stop staring at you either.

09:01.006 --> 09:03.975
Those two have been together
since the Earth cooled.

09:03.976 --> 09:05.476
Maybe there's trouble
in paradise,

09:05.477 --> 09:07.478
and it's time to let
those eyes wander.

09:07.479 --> 09:09.781
I'm not that person.
I know.

09:09.782 --> 09:13.985
It's just too bad Luke doesn't
have Adam's soulful eyes.

09:13.986 --> 09:17.088
You are terrible.

09:17.089 --> 09:20.792
I'll see you tomorrow.

09:20.793 --> 09:21.893
Hey.

09:21.894 --> 09:24.195
Hey.

09:24.196 --> 09:27.231
So what did you
think of Luke?

09:27.232 --> 09:30.067
He seems nice.

09:30.068 --> 09:33.738
You guys going to go
to the dance together?

09:33.739 --> 09:37.008
I don't know. Maybe.

